# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore  v1.0.2
# Limits the build context sent to the Docker daemon on every `docker build`.
# Without this, the 21 MB driver tarball, the entire .git/ history, and all
# runtime state directories are transferred unnecessarily every build. (#1)
# =============================================================================

# ── Git internals (never needed in image) ─────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.github/

# ── Runtime state (changes every run — busts the layer cache needlessly) ──────
cups-config/
cups-logs/
cups-spool/

# ── Local secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env

# ── Development / documentation files ────────────────────────────────────────
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
SECURITY.md
example/
*.md

# NOTE: `download/` is intentionally NOT ignored here.
# The Canon driver tarball (download/*.tar.gz) must be present in the build
# context so that the Dockerfile COPY instruction can include it in the image.
